Steam web API for node

This documentation needs work. For now read the source code. :/

var steam = require('steam').createClient('yoursteamAPIkey');

steam.getPlayerItems({}, console.log); //Returns a JSON object of Robin Walker's TF2 Backpack.

steam.getPlayerItems({gameid: 540,
                      steamid: 'A 64 bit steam Id here',
                      format: 'xml'
                    }, console.log); //Returns a raw string of the XML data requested for TF2 Beta

Supported methods:
  getPlayerItems
  getSchema
  getNewsForApp
  getGlobalAchievementPercentagesForApp
  getPlayerSummaries

  methodName ([Object], [Function]);

Each method is passed an object containing parameters and a callback function. If an empty object is given, the default parameters will be used.

